		<h2>Summary:</h2><div class="infobox">Resources are sources of <img src="/civilopediabe/images/food.png" alt="food" />Food, <img src="/civilopediabe/images/energy.png" alt="energy" />Energy, <img src="/civilopediabe/images/production.png" alt="production" />Production, <img src="/civilopediabe/images/research.png" alt="research" />Science, or <img src="/civilopediabe/images/culture.png" alt="culture" />Culture, or they provide other special bonuses. To a large degree your colony’s wealth and power will be determined by the number and variety of resources you control. To utilize a resource, it must be within your colonial borders and you must construct the appropriate “improvement” in that hex. (For example, you must construct the “Plantation” improvement to get the benefit from a “Fiber” resource.)</div>
